Title: Intelligent Database Environment for Advanced Applications IDEA Schema Evolution in OODBMS: A Selective Overview of
Note: Copyright 1994 University of Bonn ESPRIT Project 6333 Page 1  
Abstract: Summary: Based on a reduced object-oriented data model, we define a set of conditions a valid and useful schema has to satisfy. For each of these invariants, we discuss the repercussions of all schema update operations which are possible within our model, and give hints to their preservation. We give a selective overview of systems realizing schema evolution which cover the principal approaches discussed in the literature up till now. Finally, we motivate a reflective approach for schema evolution. Author(s): Thomas Lemke Contributor(s): Rainer Manthey Issued by: Rainer Manthey University of Bonn Department of Computer Science III Romerstr. 164; D-53117 Bonn; Germany Tel. +49 / 228 / 550 - 292 Authorised by: Willem Jonker Issue number: 1 Status: DEFINITIVE Date of issue: 21.9.1994 Reference: IDEA.WP.22.O.002 Number of pages: 22 
